# Hackathon Notebooks – Walkthrough

## What was built

Two Jupyter notebooks for the DIGPHAT Pharmacogenomics Hackathon:

### [01_Model_Development.ipynb](file:///Users/thechuongtrinh/Workspace/Hackathon_DIGPHAT/01_Model_Development.ipynb)
**44 cells** (21 markdown, 23 code)

| Section | Key content |
|---------|------------|
| §1 Objective | Clinical question, ccRCC + ICB + RECIST context |
| §2 Dataset Overview | Load all 5 modalities, `missingno` heatmap, cohort stats |
| §2 Integration | ssGSEA ID alignment, merge, 80/20 stratified split, save test data to `Data/test/` |
| §3 Outcome | RECIST → binary (NE dropped with explanation), class imbalance chart |
| §4 Processing | Integrated flow: RNA-seq → Mutations → Deconv → Pathways → Clinical → MICE → L1 selection → PCA |
| §5 Models | 6 classifiers (LogReg, DT, RF, SVM, XGBoost, MLP) with Stratified 5-Fold CV |
| §6 Evaluation | PR AUC, F1, MCC, confusion matrix, learning curves |
| §7–8 | Improvement ideas, feature importance |
| Save | All artifacts to `artifacts/pipeline_artifacts.joblib` |

---

### [02_Model_Deployment.ipynb](file:///Users/thechuongtrinh/Workspace/Hackathon_DIGPHAT/02_Model_Deployment.ipynb)
**21 cells** (8 markdown, 13 code)

| Section | Key content |
|---------|------------|
| Load artifacts | `joblib.load` all fitted transformers + model |
| Load test data | 5 modalities from `Data/test/` |
| Preprocessing | Apply exact same pipeline (scale, encode, impute, PCA) |
| Predict | Binary labels + probabilities |
| Report | Template for metrics when labels released |
| Submit | `requests.post` to Google Form (placeholders for entry IDs) |

